  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 190°C. Mix all the everything seed mix ingredients together in a bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pat the salmon fillets dry, then press the flesh side of each fillet into the seed mix, coating all sides except the skin."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the chickpeas, reserving the chickpea liquid. Using a vegetable peeler, peel half of the zest of the lemon."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the chickpeas and lemon zest into a baking tray, and stir the pesto through, adding a splash of the reserved chickpea liquid, until saucy. Place the salmon on top, seedy side up and transfer to the oven until cooked through, 7-10 mins (if you salmon fillets are thick, it will take a little longer)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the salmon is cooked to your liking, taste and season the chickpeas with some salt, pepper, or lemon juice - you're done! Leave to cool before storing.The cooked salmon will keep in the fridge for 3–4 days and in the freezer for up to 3 months (defrost in the fridge overnight and reheat gently in a low oven or flake it cold into dishes to avoid drying out).Eating it now? For a quick meal, enjoy with a fresh side salad, roasted veg, or rice."
    }
